## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- **[Mise](https://mise.jdx.dev/)**: Manages all tools and dependencies
- **Git**: For version control

### Installation

1. **Clone and setup**:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/{{ github_username }}/{{ project_slug }}.git
   cd {{ project_slug }}
   ./scripts/dev-setup.sh  # Installs mise if needed
   mise install            # Installs all tools
   ```

2. **Initialize the project**:

   ```bash
   mise setup              # Sets up development environment
   mise copyright          # Adds copyright headers
   ```

3. **Build and test**:

   ```bash
   mise lint-all           # Run all quality checks
   mise build-all          # Build all components
   mise test-all           # Run test suite
   ```

## Development

### Available Commands

- `mise lint-all` - Run all linters across the project
- `mise dev` - Development workflow (format, fix clippy issues, test)
- `mise format` - Format code with rustfmt
- `mise test` - Run test suite with nextest
- `mise coverage` - Generate code coverage report
- `mise audit` - Security and dependency audit
- `mise release-prep` - Prepare for release

### Project Structure

```plaintext
{{ project_slug }}/
├── core/           # Core library ({{ project_slug }}-core)
├── cli/            # Command-line tool ({{ project_slug }}-cli)
{%- if include_wasm %}
├── wasm/           # WebAssembly bindings
├── web/            # Web frontend (TypeScript)
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_python %}
├── python/         # Python bindings
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_go %}
├── go/             # Go bindings
├── go-wasm/        # Go WebAssembly bindings
{%- endif %}
├── scripts/        # Development scripts
└── mise.toml       # Task runner configuration
```

## Contributing

We welcome contributions! Please see [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) for guidelines.

### Development Workflow

1. Fork the repository
2. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feature/amazing-feature`
3. Make your changes
4. Run quality checks: `mise lint-all`
5. Commit your changes: `git commit -m 'Add amazing feature'`
6. Push to the branch: `git push origin feature/amazing-feature`
7. Open a Pull Request

